  <thing id="xDKniSumMo" name="Summon Mount" description="A death knight has the ability to summon a mount, typically a nightmare (though it may be of any other species normally used as a mount). The mount may have no more HD than 1/2 the death knight&apos;s total HD.\n\nOnce per day the death knight may magically call his mount as a full round action. It immediatly appears adjacent to the death knight and remains to serve for 2 hours per death knight HD (it may be dismissed at any time as a free action). The mount is the same creature each time it is summoned, though it may be released from service by the death knight. Each time the mount is called it appears in full health regardless of previous damage taken, and it is wearing or carrying any gear it had when dismissed.\n\nShould the mount die it immediatly disappears, leaving behind any gear it was carrying. The death knight cannot summon another mount for one month or until he gains another level, whichever comes first.\n\nCalling a mount is a conjuration (calling) effect." compset="Special" summary="Full-round to summon Nightmare or similar mount" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
