  <thing id="sDLibDLUnb" name="Unbinding" description="When you cast an {i}unbinding{/i} spell, a burst of energy erupts from your body and magically destroys any spells that contain, constrain, or seal, with the exceptions noted below.\n\nThe {i}unbinding{/i} negates {i}charm{/i} and {i}hold{/i} spells of all types, {i}arcane locks{/i} and similar closures, spells with a duration longer than instantaneous that create physical or magical barriers ({i}wall of fire{/i}, {i}wall of force{/i}), {i}guards and wards{/i}, {i}temporal stasis{/i} and {i}slow{/i} spells, among others. The effect of a {i}statue{/i} spell is ended. A {i}magic jar{/i} is shattered, forever destroyed, and the life force contained within snuffed out. In addition, any spell that holds magical effects, including other spells, immediately releases them at a range of 0 ft (including {i}magic mouth{/i}, {i}imbue with spell ability{/i}, and so on).\n\nProtective spells such as {i}protection from evil{/i}, {i}shield{/i}, {i}globe of invulnerability{/i}, and similar spells are not affected by the {i}unbinding{/i}. Petrified creatures are neither revealed nor restored. Individuals bound to service are not freed (including creatures such as familiars, invisible stalkers, genies, and planar allies). An {i}antimagic field{/i} is not affected, nor will the effects of {i}unbinding{/i} penetrate one. A {i}magic circle against evil{/i} (or other alignment) that currently holds a creature imprisoned is dispelled.\n\nCurses and {i}geas/quest{/i} spells are negated only if the caster of {i}unbinding{/i} is of equal or greater level than the original caster.\n\nAll these effects occur without regard to the caster&apos;s wishes. Spell effects on the person of the caster, being carried or worn by the caster remain undisturbed, but any others within the burst are affected, including those of allies. The opening of locks or other closures triggers any alarms or traps attached to them. Any released creature may or may not be friendly to the caster.\n\nMaterial Component: A lodestone and a pinch of saltpeter." compset="Spell" summary="a burst of energy erupts from your body and magically destroys any spells that contain, constrain, or seal">
