  <thing id="sDPesScour" name="Scourge" description="This nasty spell causes a major disease and weakness in those who fail their saving throws. Afflicted creatures are immediately (no incubation period) stricken with a sickening scourge that quickly spreads to cover thier entire bodies. The blackened boils, magenta blotches, violet lesions, seeping abscesses, and malignant cysts are excruciatingly painful and highly debilitating.\n\nThe disease deals 1d3 points of temporary Strength and Dexterity damage per day, unless the victim makes a sucessful Fortitude save on a particular day. As with mummy rot, sucessful saves do not allow the character to recover. The symptoms persist until the creature finds a magical means to cure the disease.\n\nUp to one living creature per caster level can be targetted with this spell, but no two targets may be more than 50 feet apart.\n\nFocus: A black whip or riding crop, which is cracked in the direction of the intended victims during the casting of the spell" compset="Spell">
