  <thing id="fResStreng" name="Reserves of Strength" description="When you cast a spell, you can choose to increase its effective caster level at the cost of exhausting yourself.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Iron Will, Caster level 1st\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you cast a spell, you can decide to increase your caster level with that spell by 1, 2, or 3, but you are stunned for an equal number of rounds immediately after doing so. Your increased caster level affects all level based variables of the spell, including range, area of affect, spell penetration, and the difficulty of dispelling the spell. You can exceed the normal level-fixed limits of a spell with this feat, so a 9th level wizard could use Reserves of Strength to cast a {i}fireball{/i} as a 12th level wizard and deal 12d6 fire damage.\n\nIf you are not subject to stunning effects, you instead suffer 1d6, 3d6, or 5d6 points of damage when you call upon your Reserves of Strength feat." compset="Feat" summary="Increase CL by 1-3 and exceed normal limits of spell, stun an equal # rounds." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Iron Will required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fIronWill] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Caster level 1st required."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Caster] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSpearDoom" name="Spear of Doom" description="Few can avoid death on your spearpoint when you brace yourself for their attack.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Base attack bonus +1\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you use the Ready action to set a spear or spearlike weapon against a charge, you gain a +4 bonus on your attack roll and deal double damage to a charging foe. If you use your readied action to attack a foe who enters a square you threaten without charging, you still gain the +4 bonus, but you do not deal double damage.\n\n{b}Normal:{/b} Setting a spear or similar weapon against a charge allows you to to deal double damage against a charging foe or to attack an approaching foe when he enters a square you threaten, but you do not gain any attack bonus for doing so.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} Weapons that may be set against a charge or readied in this manner include the spear, longspear, trident, halberd, and dwarven urgrosh.\n\nA fighter may select Spear of Doom as one of his fighter bonus feats." compset="Feat" summary="Gain +4 to hit when readying spear or similar weapon against a charge." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <exprreq message="Base attack bonus +1 required."><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSpeDeath" name="Spectacular Death Throes" description="Your body seethes with unchecked power, promising dire consequences to your killer.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Draconian\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Your draconian death throes are unusually powerful. When you die, your death throes have the following effects, based on your draconian race:\n    Baaz: You turn to stone the moment you die, as normal. However, on the round following your death, your statuelike corpse explodes in a blast of stony shards. All creatures within 20 feet are subjected to a ranged attack (attack bonus +10) that deals 1d10+your Con modifier damage.\n    Kapak: Instead of melting into a pool of acid, your body explodes in a 20-ft burst that deals 4d6 points of acid damage (Ref DC10 +1/2 HD + Con modifier for half)\n    Bozak: Your exploding bones deal 6d6 damage in a 20-ft burst (Ref DC10 +1/2 HD + Con modifier for half). Any creature failing its save is also knocked prone.\n    Sivak: You assume your slayer&apos;s form or burst into flame as normal, but draw life energy from your slayer to do so. Your slayer gains 1 negative level per 2 HD you have (Fort DC10 +1/2 HD + Con modifier negates)\n    Aurak: You explode in a blast of magical energy as normal, except you deal 6d6 damage in a 20-ft burst. In addition, for the next 5 rounds, you explode again on your turn, each time detonating in a spot 30 feet in a random direction from the last spot you exploded." compset="Feat" summary="Death throes are unusually powerful." uniqueness="useronce">
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Attack"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Draconian race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Draconian] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fStrafeBr" name="Strafing Breath" description="You can sustain your breath weapon when you use it on the wing, covering a larger ground area in its effects.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Fly speed, Breath Weapon, Flyby Attack, Flyby Breath\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}:  When you use your breath weapon while flying (either with a single move, using the Flyby Attack feat, or with a double move, using the Flyby Breath feat), you can extend the area covered by your breath weapon on the ground. You can use your breath weapon over a distance equal to half your fly speed, provided you move in a straight line along that distance. To determine the affected area, find the area your breath weapon would normally affct on the ground and then extend that area in a straight line the desired distance.\n\nFor example, an adult blue dragon has a fly speed of 150 feet, and it&apos;s breath weapon is a 100 foot line of lightning. Normally, its breath weapon would cover a single 5 by 5 foot square on the ground since a line is 5 feet wide and 5 feet high. Using Strafing Breath, it can cover an area 5 feet wide and 75 feet long (half its fly speed).\n\nAn old red dragon has a fly speed of 200 feet, and it&apos;s breath weapon is a 120 foot cone. If it is flying at an altitude of 80 feet, its breath weapon affects a circle on the ground with a diameter of 80 feet. Using Strafing Breath, it can cover an oblong area 80 feet wide and 180 feet long, with both ends shaped like half circles." compset="Feat" summary="Breath weapon affects greater area on ground." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment><![CDATA[@valid = 0
 if (hero.pickexists[cDDiBrth1] <> 0) then
   if (hero.child[cDDiBrth1].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] <> 0) then
      @valid = 1
    endif
   elseif (hero.pickexists[fDraBreath] <> 0) then
      @valid = 1
   elseif (hero.pickexists[rAurBrWeap] <> 0) then
      @valid = 1
endif]]></comment>
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General" name="General" abbrev="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Flyby Attack required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fFlybyAt] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Flyby Breath required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fFlyBreath] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Breath Weapon required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[xBreathWea].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] + hero.tagis[User.BreathWeap] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Fly speed required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[xFly].field[Value].value > 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fTremCharg" name="Tremendous Charge" description="You know how to use your mount&apos;s power to make your lance attacks even more deadly\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Ride 1 rank, Mounted Combat\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you employ a heavy lance in a mounted charge, you can choose to use your mount&apos;s strength score instead of your own for determining your damage bonus. \n\nFor example, if you are a human fighter with a strenght score of 14 mounted on a heavy warhorse (Strength 18), you would deal ad8+4 damage with your lance instead of 1d8+2 damage. You deal double damage for using your lance in a charge as normal.\n\nAfter you roll your attack and damage, the lance must make a DC8 Fort save or be shivered into pieces by the tremendous charge.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: Lances deal double damage on a mounted charge, but you use your own strength score to to determine the damage bonus. Lances do not have a chance to break in normal combat.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You must be armed with a heavy lance or similar weapon (such as a dragonlance). You can use this feat while mounted on a flying creature, such as a dragon.\n\nA fighter may select Tremendous Charge as one of his fighter bonus feats." compset="Feat" summary="Use mount&apos;s strength modifier for damage on charge, lance may break." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General" name="General" abbrev="General"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Fighter" name="Fighter" abbrev="Fighter"/>
    <exprreq message="Ride 1 rank required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kRide] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Mounted Combat required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fMountCom] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
