  <thing id="cInquisito" name="Inquisitor" description="By definition, an inquisitor is one who inquires, someone who hunts for people, information, or answers. The inquisitor both sees and observes, and picks up on minute details that may be missed by others. Inquisitors combine different skills that enable them to solve some of life&#146;s puzzles, from petty theft to murder. Due to their special skills, inquisitors are often employed as spies or double agents.\n\nRogues, with their understanding of the darker aspects of life, make the best inquisitors, although there are inquisitors who have been fighters, knights, clerics, and wizards. Some inquisitors specialize in certain areas, such as Wizards of High Sorcery trained to ferret out and hunt down renegades or Knights of Solamnia who investigate possible violations of the Measure. Regardless of specialty, inquisitors are often as feared as they are respected.\n\nNPC inquisitors might be members of the city watch who work to bring criminals to justice, clerics who track down heretics, or bounty hunters who bring in those with a price on their heads." compset="ClassLevel" maxlimit="10">
    <fieldval field="cHitDice" value="6"/>
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="Prestige"/>
    <tag group="ClassType" tag="Prestige"/>
    <bootstrap thing="cHelpInq"></bootstrap>
    <link linkage="helper" thing="cHelpInq"/>
    <exprreq message="Alertness required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fAlertness] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Gather Information 8 ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kGatherInf] >= 8]]></exprreq>
