  <thing id="iHamKharas" name="Hammer of Kharas" description="First called the Hammer of Honor during the Age of Dreams, the {i}Hammer of Kharas{/i} is a mighty artifact of good. It was forged by Reorx, who granted it to mortals to forge the dragonlances and to champion to cause of the dwarven race. Lost for eons, it was recovered by the dwarf Kharas shortly after the first Cataclysm. Kharas left the hammer in the Tomb of Duncan, where it remained until it was recovered by the Heroes of the Lance and was given to Hornfel. It has remained in the possession of the dwarven thane since that day.\n\nThe {i}Hammer of Kharas{/i} is a {i}+2 disruption warhammer{/i} that is intelligent (Int 11, Wis 17, Cha 20, ego 24) and can communicate via speech or telepathy. It has the following primary abilities: {i}detect evil{/i} at will, wielder is immune to fear effects, wielder gains a +4 bonus on all saving throws against spells. It has the following extraordinary powers: {i}bull&apos;s strength{/i} (on wielder) 1/day, {i}heal{/i} (on wielder) 1/day, {i}prayer{/i} 1/day, {i}protection from arrows{/i} 1/day. The hammer decides when to use any of its primary or extraordinary abilities. \n\nThe hammer&apos;s goals are to preserve the security of the dwarven race and to further the cause of good on Krynn. All dwarves immediately recognize the {i}Hammer of Kharas{/i} from tales and legends, and its wielder gains a +8 circumstance bonus on Diplomacy checks against dwarves.\n\nThe {i}Hammer of Kharas{/i} is required in the creation of {i}greater dragonlances{/i} and may be used directly with dragonmetal to forge {i}lesser dragonlances{/i}." compset="MagicWep">
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="2"/>
    <bootstrap thing="hSpellsavb"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="hImmFear"></bootstrap>
    <child entity="wSpecMagic">
      <bootstrap thing="wWarhammer"></bootstrap>
      </child>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioKeyQuina" name="Key of Quinari" description="This hand crafter music box dates back to the Age of Dreams. Small and delicate, the box opens to reveal a wooden elven female. The box is enchanted to play a haunting, ancient song, while the elven woman spins in a slow dance.\n\nPilfered from the royal palace in the Silvanesti capital, the {i}key of quinari{/i} is not what it first appears. A DC 20 bardic knowledge check reveals this object as something passed down the line of female elven royalty; it was last owned by Alhana Starbreeze.\n\nIf the check result is 25 or higher, the character knows that the object is important, actually a key created by Silvanos (the founder of the ancient elven nation) to guard something important. A legend states the {i}key of quinari{/i} will reappear at a time of great need, but its future is yet to be revealed.\n\nNo one, not even the Herald, knows at first that the music box is simply the receptacle. It&apos;s actually the music played by this heirloom that functions as the key-the box itself only serves to teach the song to its owner." compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="2"/>
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioStatuEli" name="Statue of E&apos;li" description="Statues of E&apos;li are relics imbued with divine energy, usually placed within small shrines where pilgrims may seek guidance. When the statue is touched by an individual of pure heart (good alignment), the statue glows with a flickering radiance (as the {i}continual flame{/i} spell). Anything bathed in the light is treated as if under the effects of a {i}consecrate{/i} spell (this only functions during one of the eras in which the gods are active in Krynn). Any creatures filled with evil intend touching the statue is burned by the flickering light (which inflicts 1s4 points of damage during eras where the deities are not active, or 2d4 damage when the gods are present).\n\nA secondary function of these statues is to allow petitioners to directly petition the gods of Light to be accepted as a cleric. If the petitioner is true, then the statue will create for them a medallion of faith\n\nModerate divination and evocation; CL 9th; Craft Wonderous Item, {i}consecrate{/i}, {i}continual flame{/i}, {i}commune{/i}; Price 12,000 stl; Weight 5 lbs; Cost to Create 6,000 stl +480 XP" compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="5"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="12000"/>
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iGhostBlad" name="Ghost Blade" description="Also known as {i}Alurashaen{/i}, the Ghost Blade is a truly strange looking sword. This mottled gray and silver blade functions as a normal {i}+1 longsword{/i} for attack and damage purposes. However, while it is unsheathed, the blade generates a flickering aura about its wielder. This aura causes the wielder to appear shadowy and indistinct, as well as muffling surrounding sound, granting the wielder a +10 circumstance bonus on Hide and Move Silently checks as long as the blade is unsheathed. This ability functions as long as the wielder has not struck with the blade; once the blade has been used in an attack (successful or not), it must be resheathed and drawn again to create the hiding effect.\n\nFaint illusion; CL 5th; Craft Magic Arms and Armor, improved invisibility, silence; Price 15,000 stl; Weight 3 lbs.; Cost to Create 7,500 stl +600 XP" compset="MagicWep">
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="1"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="15000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="3"/>
    <bootstrap thing="hGhostHide"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[       if (field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
         #applybonus[ModCirc, hero.child[kHide], 10]
         #applybonus[ModCirc, hero.child[kMoveSil], 10]
          endif]]></eval>
    <child entity="wSpecMagic">
      <bootstrap thing="wLongsword"></bootstrap>
      </child>
    </thing>
  <thing id="hGhostHide" name="+10 to Hide/Move SIlently" description="From unsheathing until first used to attack, the wielder has a +10 circumstance bonus to Hide and Move Silently." compset="Special" summary="Draw until first attack, wielder gains +10 circ bonus to Hide/Move Silently.">
    <fieldval field="xSource" value="Ghost Blade"/>
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpSourceEq"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iDragonLan" name="Dragonlance, Lesser" description="A {i}lesser dragonlance{/i} is a {i}+2 dragon bane lance{/i} than glows with a soft light (not bright enough to provide any actual illumination). A {i}lesser dragonlance{/i} has hardness 17 and 40 hit points.\n\nIt has a magic enhancement bonus of only +1, which is superceded by the natural enhancement bonus (+2) of the dragonmetal from which it is made.\n\n{i}Lesser dragonlances{/i} can only be created using silver dragonmetal from the great Stone Dragon of Ergoth, and must be forged using either the {i}SIlver Arm of Ergoth{/i}, or the {i}Hammer of Kharas{/i}. If a {i}dragonlance{/i} is forged with both artifacts, it is a {i}greater dragonlance{/i}. The secret of forging {i}dragonlances{/i} is god-granted, whether the deities choose to teach it directly or through the power of the {i}Silver Arm{/i}.\n\nStrong conjuration; CL 8th; divine instruction; Price equivalent 17,310 stl" compset="MagicWep">
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="2"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="17310"/>
    <child entity="wSpecMagic">
      <bootstrap thing="wLance"></bootstrap>
      </child>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iGrDragonL" name="Dragonlance, Greater" description="A {i}greater dragonlance{/i} (or &quot;true&quot; {i}dragonlance{/i}) can only be forged from pure dragonmetal, using both the {i}Silver Arm of Ergoth{/i} and the {i}hammer of Kharas{/i}. These weapons are blessed by the divine powers of Good, and evil beings that try to touch or wield a {i}greater dragonlance{/i} do so only at a price.\n\nA {i}greater dragonlance{/i} is a {i}+4 dragon bane lance{/i} than glows with a soft light (not bright enough to provide any actual illumination). A {i}greater dragonlance{/i} has hardness 23 and 70 hit points.\n\nWhen used against an evil dragon, a {i}greater dragonlance{/i} deals 1 point of permanent Constitution drain with every hit, in addition to the lance&apos;s normal damage and the bonus bane damage. If the wielder scores a critical hit against an evil dragon, the lance deals a number of points of permanent Constitution drain equal to the character level of the wielder.\n\nThe {i}greater dragonlance{/i} bestows two negative levels on any evil creature attempting to wield it. The negative levels remain as long as the weapon is held and disappears when it is no longer wielded. The negative levels never results in actual level loss, but cannot be overcome in any way (including {i}restoration{/i} spells) while the weapon is wielded.\n\nStrong conjuration; CL 20th; divine instruction; Price equivalent 107,310 stl" compset="MagicWep">
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="4"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="107310"/>
    <child entity="wSpecMagic">
      <bootstrap thing="wLance"></bootstrap>
      </child>
    </thing>
