  <thing id="sMysMinCre" name="Minor Creation" description="You create a nonmagical, unattended object of nonliving, vegetable matter&#151;linen clothes, a hemp rope, a wooden ladder, and so forth. The volume of the item created cannot exceed 1 cubic foot per caster level. You must succeed on an appropriate skill check to make a complex item, such as Craft (bow making) check to make straight arrow shafts.\n\nAttempting to use any created object as a material component causes the spell to fail.\n\n{i}Material Component{/i}: A tiny piece of matter of the same sort of item you plan to create with {i}minor creation{/i}&#151;a bit of twisted hemp to create rope, and so forth." compset="Spell" summary="Creates one cloth or wood object.">
