  <thing id="sMysHarden" name="Hardening" description="This spell increases the hardness of materials (see Table 8-12: Substance Hardness and Hit Points in the PH). Paper becomes harder to tear, glass becomes harder to break, wood becomes more resilient, and so on. For every two caster level, increase by 1 the hardness of the material targeted by the spell. This hardness increase improves only the material&apos;s resistance to damage. Nothing else is modified by the improvement. \n\nFor example, a longsword (normal hardness 10) modified by a {i}hardening{/i} spell cast by a 12th level caster would have hardness 16 for purposes of ignoring damage caused by someone using the sunder action. The sword&apos;s hit points, attack and damage modifiers, and other characteristics are not affected. Nor does {i}hardening{/i} provide resistance to other forms of transformation; ice still melts, wood or paper still burn, stone is still transmuted to mud with the proper spell, and so on.\n\nThis spell affects up to 10 cubic feet per caster level. If cast upon a metal or mineral, the volume is reduced to 1 cubic foot per level.\n\nMaterial Component: A pinch of diamond dust worth at least 100 gp per cubic foot of the item to be hardened." compset="Spell">
