  <thing id="sMysBiCrHa" name="Bigby&apos;s Crushing Hand" description="This spell functions like {i}Bigby&#146;s interposing hand{/i}, except that the hand can interpose itself, push, or crush one opponent that you select.\n\nThe {i}crushing hand{/i} can grapple an opponent like {i}Bigby&#146;s grasping hand{/i} does. Its grapple bonus equals your caster level + your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma modifier (for a wizard, cleric, or sorcerer, respectively), +12 for the hand&#146;s Strength score (35), +4 for being Large. The hand deals 2d6+12 points of damage (lethal, not nonlethal) on each successful grapple check against an opponent.\n\nThe {i}crushing hand{/i} can also interpose itself as {i}Bigby&#146;s interposing hand{/i} does, or it can bull rush an opponent as {i}Bigby&#146;s forceful hand{/i} does, but at a +18 bonus.\n\nDirecting the spell to a new target is a move action.\n\nClerics who cast this spell name it for their deities&#151;{i}St. Cuthbert&#146;s crushing hand{/i}, for example.\n\n{i}Arcane Material Component{/i}: The shell of an egg.\n\n{i}Arcane Focus{/i}: A glove of snakeskin." compset="Spell" summary="Large hand provides cover, pushes, or crushes your foes.">
