  <thing id="sMysBiGrHa" name="Bigby&apos;s Grasping Hand" description="This spell functions like {i}Bigby&#146;s interposing hand{/i}, except the hand can also grapple one opponent that you select. The {i}grasping hand{/i} gets one grapple attack per round. Its attack bonus to make contact equals your caster level + your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma modifier (for wizards, clerics, and sorcerers, respectively), +10 for the hand&#146;s Strength score (31), &#150;1 for being Large. Its grapple bonus is this same figure, except with a +4 modifier for being Large instead of &#150;1. The hand holds but does not harm creatures it grapples. Directing the spell to a new target is a move action.\n\nThe {i}grasping hand{/i} can also bull rush an opponent as {i}Bigby&#146;s forceful hand{/i} does, but at a +16 bonus on the Strength check (+10 for Strength 35, +4 for being Large, and a +2 bonus for charging, which it always gets), or interpose itself as {i}Bigby&#146;s interposing{/i} hand does.\n\nClerics who cast this spell name it for their deities&#151;{i}Kord&#146;s grasping hand{/i}, for example.\n\n{i}Arcane Focus{/i}: A leather glove." compset="Spell" summary="Hand provides cover, pushes, or grapples.">
