  <thing id="cRightZeal" name="Righteous Zealot" description="The righteous zealot is a person with a cause that directs every aspect of his life. So important is this cause to the righteous zealot that he goes among the masses to spread the word of his beliefs, hoping to bring others into the fold. Righteous zealots see themselves as saviors. Nonbelievers may view them either with amusement or with justifiable concern. A righteous zealot who grows too powerful can dictate the destiny of nations.\n\nBards and clerics become righteous zealots&#151;bards because of their mastery of the spoken word and clerics because of their unwavering belief and faith. Unfortunately, righteous zealots may become so caught up in their causes that they become blinded by their own glory, as evidenced by the Kingpriest of Istar, whose arrogance and zeal brought about the Cataclysm that reshaped the entire world.\n\nNPC righteous zealots are leaders of cults, such as the Seekers of Abanasinia, or fanatical followers of any deity or ideology. They are manipulators, with an army of followers who are fanatically loyal. Once a righteous zealot has a cause, he does not allow anything or anyone to stand in his way." compset="ClassLevel" maxlimit="10">
    <fieldval field="cHitDice" value="6"/>
    <usesource source="DLCS"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="Prestige"/>
    <tag group="ClassType" tag="Prestige"/>
    <bootstrap thing="cHelpRiZ"></bootstrap>
    <link linkage="helper" thing="cHelpRiZ"/>
    <exprreq message="Bluff 3 ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kBluff] >= 3]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Concentration 8 ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kConcent] >= 8]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Diplomacy 8 ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kDiplomacy] >= 8]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Sense Motive 4 ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kSenseMot] >= 4]]></exprreq>
    <prereq message="Perform (any) 3 ranks required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[~ Loop through all perform skills
var result as number
foreach pick in hero where "Helper.SkCatPerf"

~ If this skill has 3 or more ranks, we are valid
  if (each.field[kUserRanks].value >= 3) then
    result += 1
  endif
nexteach

if (result >= 1) then
  @valid = 1
  endif]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRiZOratio" name="Oration" description="Once per day per level , a righteous zealot may use his command of the spoken language in much the same way a bard is able to use music to sway others. Depending upon how many ranks he has in the Diplomacy skill, he can enthrall crowds, cause people to question their beliefs, compel an individual to undertake actions he wouldn&apos;t normally do, confuse an opponent through debate, and inflame crowds into bloodthirsty rage. \n\nThe righteous zealot must be able to speak clearly and be heard to use this ability properly. As with casting a spell a deaf righteous zealot suffers a 20% chance to fail with oration. If he fails, the attempt still counts against his daily limit." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Use Diplomacy to influence crowd for various effects." sortorder="1">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1" name="1" abbrev="1"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge" name="ShowCharge" abbrev="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRiZ"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10000">field[hTotal].value += hero.child[cHelpRiZ].field[cTotalLev].value</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRiZEnthDi" name="Oration: Enthralling Discourse" description="Requires 8 ranks in Diplomacy. \n\nA righteous zealot can use his oration to sway groups of people, causing them to pause in their activities to listen to his words. The ability to speak before large crowds and control the abb and flow of sentiment is perhaps the most potent tool of the zealot. The crowd to be enthralled must be within 90 feet, and able to see, hear and understand (speak the same language) the righteous zealot. The zealot makes a Diplomacy check, and each target can negate the effect with a sucessful WIll save, DC equal to the zealot&apos;s check result.\n\nIf the save fails, the target sits or stands queitly and listens to the zealot&apos;s words as long as he continues to speak and concentrate (to a max of 2 rounds per level of the righteous zealot). The effects are otherwise identical to an {i}enthrall{/i} spell.\n\nEnthralling discourse is an Enchantment (Charm [Language-Dependant, Mind-Affecting, Sonic] ability." compset="ClSpecial" summary="{i}Enthrall{/i} crowd in 90 ft (DC = Diplomacy roll, Will neg) for max X rds." sortorder="1">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1" name="1" abbrev="1"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRiZ"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
      ~ If we don't have enough ranks in Diplomacy, we're not available
      if (#skillranks[kDiplomacy] < 8) then
        var result as number
        result = assign[Helper.SpcDisable]
        endif

     var duration as number
     duration = #levelcount[RightZeal] * 2

field[xSumm].text = "{i}Enthrall{/i} crowd in 90 ft for max " & duration & " rds (DC = Diplomacy roll, Will neg)."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRiZComArg" name="Oration: Compelling Argument" description="Requires 9 ranks in Diplomacy. \n\nA righteous zealot can use his oration to present a compelling argument, convincing a single person to see things his way, at least temporarily. This ability acts as a {i}suggestion{/i} spell, and can only be used on an individual who has either been enthralled (by enthralling discourse) or confused (by verbal obfuscation).\n\nThe suggestion does not count against the righteous zealot&apos;s daily limit on oration, but the enthralling or confusion does. A Will saving through (DC 10+ the righteous zealot&apos;s class level + Cha modifier) negates the effect. \n\nCompelling argument is an Enchantment (Compulsion) [Language-Dependant, Mind-Affecting, Sonic] ability." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Plant {i}suggestion{/i} in enthralled/ confused target (DCXX Will neg)." sortorder="2">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="2"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRiZ"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
      ~ If we don't have enough ranks in Diplomacy, we're not available
      if (#skillranks[kDiplomacy] < 9) then
        var result as number
        result = assign[Helper.SpcDisable]
      endif

     var DC as number
     DC = 10 + #levelcount[RightZeal] + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value
field[xSumm].text = "Plant {i}suggestion{/i} in enthralled/confused target (DC" & DC & " Will neg)."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRiZConTir" name="Oration: Condemning Tirade" description="Requires 13 ranks in Diplomacy. \n\nA righteous zealot can use his oration to exploit weaknesses in other people. By verbally unleashing his anger against an individual, the righteous zealot can cause an opponent to question himself. The target is allowed a Will save (DC 10 + righteous zealot class level + Cha modifier) to avoid becoming shaken for 10 minutes per level of the righteous zealot.\n\nCondemning Tirade is an Enchantment (Charm) [Language-Dependant, Mind-Affecting, Sonic] ability." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Target questions self and is shaken for XX min (DCYY Will neg)." sortorder="5">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="5"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRiZ"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
      ~ If we don't have enough ranks in Diplomacy, we're not available
      if (#skillranks[kDiplomacy] < 13) then
        var result as number
        result = assign[Helper.SpcDisable]
      endif

     var DC as number
     DC = 10 + #levelcount[RightZeal] + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value
     var duration as number
     duration = #levelcount[RightZeal] * 10

field[xSumm].text = "Target questions self and is shaken for " & duration & " min (DC" & DC & " Will neg)."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRiZVerbOb" name="Oration: Verbal Obfuscation" description="Requires 16 ranks in Diplomacy. \n\nA righteous zealot can use his oration to trap a single individual within a web of words. The victim is allowed a Will save (DC 12 + righteous zealot class level + Cha modifier) to avoid becoming confused for 1 minute per level of the righteous zealot.\n\nVerbal Obfuscation is an Enchantment (Compulsion) [Language-Dependant, Mind-Affecting, Sonic] ability." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Web of words entrap subject, is confused 1 min/level if fail save." sortorder="8">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="8"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRiZ"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
      ~ If we don't have enough ranks in Diplomacy, we're not available
      if (#skillranks[kDiplomacy] < 16) then
        var result as number
        result = assign[Helper.SpcDisable]
        endif

     var DC as number
     DC = 12 + #levelcount[RightZeal] + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value
field[xSumm].text = "Web of words entrap foe, causing {i}confusion{/i} for " & #levelcount[RightZeal] & " min (DC" & DC & " Will neg)."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRiZInfOra" name="Oration: Inflammatory Oratory" description="Requires 18 ranks in Diplomacy. \n\nThe righteous zealot gains near total mastery over crowds. Once he has a crowd enthralled, he is able to inspire extremes of emotion within every person in the crowd, mimicking the effects of one of the following spells: {i}crushing despair{/i}, {i}good hope{/i}, or {i}rage{/i}. The emotion last as long as the zighteous zealot continues to direct the ebb and flow of emotions (as long as he maintains his enthralling discourse), though each victim is allowed a Will save vs the zealot&apos;s Diplomacy check to resist the effect.\n\nInflammatory Oratory is an Enchantment (Compulsion) [Language-Dependant, Mind-Affecting, Sonic] ability." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Inspire {i}crushing despair{/i}, {i}good hope{/i} or {i}rage{/i} in enthralled crowd." sortorder="10">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="10"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRiZ"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
      ~ If we don't have enough ranks in Diplomacy, we're not available
      if (#skillranks[kDiplomacy] < 18) then
        var result as number
        result = assign[Helper.SpcDisable]
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRiZRIndig" name="Righteous Indignation" description="Filled with a sense of self-worth and virtue, a righteous zealot will not deviate from a given path. Once per day, the righteous zealot may add his charisma modifier to any one saving throw. \n\nThe righteous zealot gains another use of this ability at 4th and 7th level." compset="ClSpecial" summary="X/day, add Charisma modifier as bonus to one saving throw." sortorder="1">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpRiZ"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="10000"><![CDATA[~ Generate our new name
      var level as number
      level = field[xTotalLev].value

      var total as number
      if (level >= 7) then
        total = 3
      elseif (level >= 4) then
        total = 2
      else
        total = 1
        endif

      field[hTotal].value += total

      field[xSumm].text = "" & field[hTotal].value & "/day, add Charisma modifier as bonus to one saving throw."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cRiZRIndi2" name="Righteous Indignation (2/day)" description="Gain another daily use of Righteous Indignation." compset="ClSpecial" sortorder="4">
