  <thing id="sClrDivRet" name="Divine Retribution" description="You select a single form of attack (acid, cold, electricity, fire, or force) when you cast this spell. For the duration of the spell, any attack based upon that element that strikes the caster is absorbed and instantly reflected upon the originator of the attack. Effect, area, and touch range spells, spell like abilities, and supernatural abilities that use the named form of energy are all equally affected. When it is reflected, the effect is altered, becoming either Sacred or Profane (depending on the alignment of the cleric&apos;s deity). Thus a creature that may normally be immune to its own attacks may now be vulnerable instead. This Sacred/Profane attack is equally effect, regardless of the alignment of the originator.\n\nFor example, a cleric of Sargonnas (a Lawful Evil deity) casts {i}divine retribution{/i} upon herself, selecting fire to be protected against, knowing she is to face a red dragon. When the dragon uses his fire breath, the {i}divine retribution{/i} absorbs the damage and returns it upon the dragon as a Profane attack. Though it resembles the same fiery breath and the dragon&apos;s alignment is Chaotic Evil, the returned Profane damage is not reduced. The creature is still allowed spell resistance and a saving throw against its own attack." compset="Spell">
    <fieldval field="sRange" value="Personal"/>
