  <thing id="sSorElemDa" name="Elemental Dart" description="From raw elemental matter, you form a magical dart of energy that streaks forward and strikes the target you designate. You choose to creat an acid, cold, electricity, or fire dart upon casting the spell. You must succeed at a ranged touch attack to hit your target. The dart deals 1d6+1 point per caster level (max 1d6+10). A creature struck by an {i}elemental dart{/i} may attempt a Fort save for half damage.\n\nYou can&apos;t single out specific parts of a creature to attack. Unlike with magic missile, you can damage inanimate objects with an {i}elemental dart{/i}.\n\nAt every odd caster level after 3rd you gain an additional dart (up to a maximum of 5 darts at 11th level). You can attack with multiple darts in the same action used to cast the spell, targetting a single or several targets (no two of which can be more than 30 feet apart). You must designate targets before making attack rolls, checking against spell resistance, or rolling damage.\n\nSince the darts are composed of elemental energy, they may deal greater damage against foes vulnerable to certain energy types. Additionally, foes may be protected against the {i}elemental darts{/i} by energy resistance." compset="Spell">
