  <thing id="sWizFiPort" name="Fistandantilus&apos;s Portal" description="Casting {i}Fistandantilus&apos;s portal{/i} opens an interdimensional connection between two places on the same plane of existance, allowing travel between the locations in either direction. \n\nThe portal itself is a circular disk from 5 to 20 feet in diameter (caster&apos;s choice), oriented in the direction you desire when it comes into existance (typically vertical and facing you). It is a two dimensional window and anyone or anything that moves through is shunted instantly to the other side. The portal has a front and back. Creatures moving through the portal from the front are transported to the other location, those moving from the back are not.\n\nThe interdimensional connection is forged through the Astral Plane, so anything preventing Astral travel will also block the usage of the portal. Much like the {i}teleport{/i} spell, you must have a clear idea of the location and layout of the destination. You can&apos;t create a portal if you don&apos;t know where the terminus will end up. The clearer your mental image, the more likely the portal will form. Areas of strong physical or magical energies may make traversing a portal more hazardous or even impossible. Use the following table to determine the sucess of the portal&apos;s opening:\n\nDestination Familiarity         Sucessful Portal     Failed Portal\nVery familiar                                    01-97                       98-100\nStudied carefully                            01-94                       95-100\nSeen casually                                 01-88                       89-100\nViewed once                                   01-76                       77-100\nDescription                                      01-60                       61-100" compset="Spell">
