  <thing id="sWizLighTr" name="Magius&apos;s Light of Truth" description="The spell used by Palin to help defeat Chaos during the Chaos War, {i}Magius&apos;s light of truth{/i} was developed by the famous war-mage during the time of Huma, though it had never before been used until it was given to Palin by his uncle, the archmage Raistlin Majere, with the permission of the Orders of High Sorcery.\n\nWhen this spell is cast, it creates a 120 foot long, radiant cone of pure light, drawing it from the spirit of the spellcaster and channeling it through an artifact of light. Against nonlawful creatures, the spell has multiple effects, depending on the creature&apos;s alignment.\n\nIf the spellcaster is on his home plane, non-lawful extraplanar creatures within the area are instantly banished back to thier home plane. Creatures so banished cannot return for at least one day per caster level.\n\nAny creatures of neutrality (neutral good, neutral, neutral evil) caught within the cone of light are dazed 1d6 rounds and are dealt 3d6 damage (a sucessful will save negates the daze and halves the damage).\n\nAgainst creatures of chaos (chaotic good, chaotic neutral, chaotic evil) {i}light of truth{/i} deals 1d6 damage per caster level (max 25d6), or half damage with a sucessful Will save. If the creature fails its will save, it is subject to additional effects depending upon it&apos;s HD:\n\nHD                             Effect\n15 or more             Dazed\nLess than 15         Stunned, dazed\nLess than 10         Paralyzed, stunned, dazed\nLess than 5           Killed, paralyzed, stunned, dazed\n\nThe effects are cumulative.\n{b}Dazed:{/b} The creature is dazed 1d6 rounds\n{b}Stunned:{/b} The creature is stunned 2d6 rounds\n{b}Paralyzed:{/b} The creature is paralyzed for 2d6 minutes\n{b}Killed:{/b} Living creatures die, Constructs and undead creatures are destroyed\n\nFocus: An artifact or intelligent magic item (minimum caster level 15th) of lawful alignment\n\nXP Cost: 500 XP" compset="Spell">
