  <thing id="sWizSpShie" name="Spark Shield" description="This spell surrounds you in an aura of crackling electricity, both offering protection against electricity attacks as well as causing damage to each creature who attacks you in melee.\n\nAny creature striking you with its body or a handheld weapon deals normal damage, but at the same time the attacker takes 1d4 points of electricity damage +1 per caster level (max 1d4+15). If the strike you with a metal weapon, are wearing metal armor, or carrying a lot of metal, the take 2d4 +2 per caster level (max 2d4+15).\n\nIf a creature has spell resistance, it applies to this damage. Creatures wielding reach weapons do not take damage unless thier weapon is at least 1/2 metal.\n\nAgainst electrical attacks, you take only half damage. If the attack allows a Reflex save for half damage, you take no damage on a successful save.\n\nWhen casting this spell, you appear to be sheathed in tiny lightning bolts that undulate across the body. This provides light equal to a torch, and the caster can choose the hue of the light, though the default is blue-white.\n\nMaterial Component: Two thin copper bracelets, one worn on each wrist." compset="Spell">
