  <thing id="sWizSpWalk" name="Spirit Walk" description="By focusing your energy, you are able to seperate your spirit from your body, allowing it to travel anywhere on the same plane of existence. Distance is not a factor, but the local to be visited by your spirit form must be known - a place familiar to you. While in your spirit form, you can see and hear things, just as if you were there. You can also be seen and be heard, though you are unable to actually interact in that location. You cannot cast spells through your spirit form, nor does it allow magically enhanced senses to work through it. \n\nIf the chosen locale is magically dark, you see nothing. If it is naturally pitch black you can see up to 10 feet away. Lead sheeting or magical protections (such as {i}antimagic field{/i}, {i}mind blank{/i}, or {i}nondetection{/i}) blocks you from noticing individuals in the area you have travelled to, though you can feel that your senses are being blocked somehow.\n\nWhile your spirit is out of your body it is paralyzed and completely helpless." compset="Spell">
