  <thing id="sWizStormW" name="Storm Wall" description="An immobile, sparking curtain of radiant electricity springs into existence (sheet 20 feet long/level or ring with radius 5 ft/2 caster levels, either 20 feet high). One side of the wall, selected by you, sends forth miniature bolts of lightning, causing 2d4 points of electricity damage to all within 10 feet, and 1d4 damage to those 10 to 20 feet away. The wall deals this damage when it appears and each round that a creature remains within the area.\n\nAny creature passing through the storm wall takes 2d4 +1 point per caster level (max 2d4+20). Creatures made of metal, wearing metal armor, or carrying lots of metal take double damage when passing through the wall.\n\nIf you evoke the wall so that it appears where creatures are, each creature takes damage as though passing through the wall. Such creatures can make a Reflex save to avoid the wall, ending up on a random side (if on the sparking side they take 2d4 damage as normal).\n\nThe storm wall spell can be smothered by using enough dirt or sand to ground the electricity. For each cubic foot of sand used, one corresponding foot of the wall can be smothered.\n\nMaterial Component: A lodestone" compset="Spell">
